International Environmental Standards Applied in East China
SUZHOU , December 28 ( Xinhua ) -- A set of international standards for environmental management , known as ISO14000 , has been applied on an experimental basis in a hi-tech development area of the city of Suzhou in east China 's Jiangsu Province .
The standards will help improve the environmental management system and offer valuable experience for other places in China , said an official from the State Environmental Protection Administration ( SEPA ) .
All the enterprises in the pilot area must make plans , monitor the environment , and control pollution according to these international standards , said the environmental official .
A development-area official said they will submit their report on the application of the new standards to the SEPA next June .
